# CODEOWNERS — Ownership matrix for automatic PR review requests.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# The LAST matching pattern wins, so order matters: most-specific rules go last.
#
# Replace placeholders with real GitHub handles / team slugs before merging:
#   arananet  — org or user that owns the repo
#   arananet     — maintainer team slug (e.g. core-maintainers)

# ── Default owners: every file not matched below
*                               @arananet/arananet

# ── OpenSpec configuration and specs: governance-critical
/.openspec/                     @arananet/arananet
/.openspec/config.yaml          @arananet/arananet
/.openspec/specs/               @arananet/arananet

# ── CI/CD, security workflows, and repo-wide GitHub config
/.github/                       @arananet/arananet
/.github/workflows/             @arananet/arananet
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @arananet/arananet
/.github/dependabot.yml         @arananet/arananet

# ── Claude Code skills, hooks, and settings
/.claude/                       @arananet/arananet

# ── Git hooks and repo bootstrap
/hooks/                         @arananet/arananet
/setup.sh                       @arananet/arananet

# ── Governance documents
/SECURITY.md                    @arananet/arananet
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md             @arananet/arananet
/CONTRIBUTING.md                @arananet/arananet
/LICENSE                        @arananet/arananet

# ── Agent / AI instructions — changes here affect every future contribution
/CLAUDE.md                      @arananet/arananet
/.github/AGENTS.md              @arananet/arananet
/.github/copilot-instructions.md @arananet/arananet
/.github/agents/                @arananet/arananet
